PRESIDENT Jacob Zuma has signed two proclamations authorising the special investigating unit (SIU) to investigate the Gauteng health department and the Department of Rural Development and Land Reform.The SIU will investigate allegations that the procurement by the department of services of 28 non-governmental organisations in whose care mental healthcare users were entrusted and payments made in respect thereof in a manner that was not fair, transparent, equitable and contrary to applicable legislation .The SIU will also probe whether there were any unlawful, improper acts or omissions by officials of the department or owner or staff of the 28 entities and whether the department incurred unauthorised, irregular or fruitless and wasteful expenditure.The non-performance by the 28 NGOs, serious maladministration in connection with the affairs of the department, improper or unlawful conduct by the officials or employees of the department and unlawful, irregular or unapproved acquisitive act, transaction, measure or practice having a bearing upon state property, will also be investigated.At the Department of Rural Development and Land Reform, the SIU will examine the acquisition by the department of certain farms and the identification, selection and appointment of the strategic partners and beneficiaries for such farms in a manner that was not fair, transparent, equitable and contrary to applicable legislation .The SIU will investigate the alleged misappropriation of recapitalisation funds in terms of the department s recapitalisation and development programme and any improper or unlawful conduct by officials of the department or any other person or entity.DENNIS CRUYWAGENdennisc@thenewage.co.za